weather_detail.description: Moderate east and north winds with minor snow transport

Between noon on March 3 and 14:00 on March 4, 2023 Highlands Peak weather station recorded consistent wind speeds between 10-20 miles per hour (mph) with inconsistent direction varying between northwest, west, and southwest directions. Starting at about 15:00 on March 4 the wind speeds dramatically increased coming from a consistent southwest direction up to 30-40 mph with gusts reaching over 60mph.
